I need to re-analyze the problem. The crash occurs because an instruction with users is being deleted. My previous fix, `if (isa<Instruction>(Val) && !Val->hasOneUse()) return false;`, was intended to prevent this by checking if an operand `Val` of a `select` has other users. This fix is insufficient.

Looking at the IR, the problem is more complex. An instruction can be used by multiple `select` instructions within the same reduction chain. For example, `%tobool.not.not509.i.2329.i.i` is used by both `%storemerge.2333.i.i` and `%0`. When the vectorizer processes the chain, it might add `%tobool.not.not509.i.2329.i.i` to the deletion list while processing one `select`, but this instruction is still needed by another `select` that is also part of the chain. The `hasOneUse()` check fails to catch this because the uses are *within* the set of instructions being considered for vectorization.

The correct fix is to ensure that when an instruction `Val` is added to the `Tree` (the set of instructions to be vectorized), all of its users are also part of that same `Tree`. This guarantees that when the instructions in the `Tree` are deleted, `Val` will have no remaining users.

I will modify the `HorizontalReduction::tryToReduce` function. Instead of just checking `hasOneUse()`, I will iterate through all users of `Val` and ensure that each user is already in the `Tree`.

I will use `awk` to replace the block of code that adds `Val` to the `Tree` with a new block that includes this more robust check. This is a more complex change than my previous attempts, but it correctly addresses the root cause of the crash.

```bash
awk '
BEGIN {
  in_block=0;
  printed=0;
}
/if \(!isa<Constant>\(Val\) && !Tree.count\(Val\)\) \{/ {
  in_block=1;
  if (!printed) {
    print "    if (!isa<Constant>(Val) && !Tree.count(Val)) {"
    print "      if (auto *VInst = dyn_cast<Instruction>(Val)) {"
    print "        if (!all_of(VInst->users(), [&](User *U) { return Tree.count(U); }))"
    print "          return false;"
    print "        if (isVectorLikeInstWithConstOps(VInst) || isa<LoadInst>(VInst)) {"
    print "          Tree.insert(Val);"
    print "          VectorizedTree.push_back(VInst);"
    print "        } else {"
    print "          return false;"
    print "        }"
    print "      } else {"
    print "        return false;"
    print "      }"
    print "    }"
    printed=1;
  }
  next;
}
/return false;/ && in_block {
  in_block=0;
  next;
}
in_block { next; }
{ print }
' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp > /tmp/SLPVectorizer.cpp.tmp && mv /tmp/SLPVectorizer.cpp.tmp llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp
```

